fields.title: Advanced Mathematics - Calculus & Algebra
fields.description: Comprehensive mathematics tutoring covering calculus, algebra, and trigonometry for high school and early college students. Personalized approach with practice problems and exam preparation.
fields.subject: Mathematics

fields.title: Physics Fundamentals - Mechanics & Thermodynamics
fields.description: Learn the fundamentals of physics including mechanics, thermodynamics, and electromagnetism. Perfect for students preparing for AP Physics or college entrance exams.
fields.subject: Physics

fields.title: Organic Chemistry Mastery
fields.description: Master organic chemistry concepts including reaction mechanisms, stereochemistry, and synthesis. Ideal for pre-med students and chemistry majors.
fields.subject: Chemistry

fields.title: Statistics & Probability for Data Science
fields.description: Learn statistical concepts, probability theory, and data analysis techniques. Perfect for students interested in data science and machine learning.
fields.subject: Statistics

fields.title: English Literature & Writing
fields.description: Improve your English literature analysis skills and creative writing abilities. Covers poetry, prose, and essay writing techniques.
fields.subject: English

fields.title: Introduction to Calculus
fields.description: Basic concepts of calculus including limits, derivatives, and their applications. Understanding the fundamental theorem of calculus.

fields.title: Differential Calculus
fields.description: Advanced differentiation techniques, chain rule, product rule, and quotient rule. Applications in optimization problems.

fields.title: Integral Calculus
fields.description: Integration techniques, substitution method, integration by parts, and applications of integrals in area and volume calculations.

fields.title: Linear Algebra Basics
fields.description: Matrix operations, systems of linear equations, and vector spaces. Foundation for advanced mathematics.

fields.title: Newton's Laws of Motion
fields.description: Understanding the three fundamental laws of motion and their applications in solving physics problems.

fields.title: Energy and Work
fields.description: Concepts of kinetic energy, potential energy, work-energy theorem, and conservation of energy.

fields.title: Thermodynamics Basics
fields.description: First and second laws of thermodynamics, heat engines, and entropy concepts.

fields.title: Calculus Problem Set 1
fields.description: Complete 20 differentiation problems focusing on basic rules and chain rule applications. Show all work and explain your reasoning.

fields.title: Optimization Project
fields.description: Solve 5 real-world optimization problems using calculus. Include graphical analysis and interpretation of results.

fields.title: Integration Techniques Practice
fields.description: Practice various integration techniques including substitution, integration by parts, and partial fractions. Complete the assigned worksheet.

fields.title: Mechanics Problem Set
fields.description: Solve 15 problems involving Newton's laws, friction, and circular motion. Include free body diagrams for each problem.

fields.title: Energy Conservation Lab Report
fields.description: Write a detailed lab report on the pendulum experiment demonstrating conservation of mechanical energy. Include data analysis and error discussion.

fields.title: Thermodynamics Case Study
fields.description: Research and present a case study on a real-world application of thermodynamics (heat engines, refrigeration, etc.). 5-page written report required.
